The paper discusses the use of die-stacked DRAM in modern big-data applications, which involves topics related to computer architecture, distributed computing, and operating systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AR (Computer Architecture), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DB (Databases), cs.OS (Operating Systems), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
